<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,222,535]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,438,463]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was firstly described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[906,1034,438,462]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Evergestis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caesialis">
<emphasis box="[906,1034,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">E. caesialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation box="[1075,1231,438,463]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref19096" refString="Amsel, H. G. (1953) Die Microlepidopteren der Brandt'schen Iran-Ausbeute. 4. Teil. Arkiv for Zoologie (N. S.), Stockholm 6 (16), 255 - 326." type="journal article">Amsel (1953)</bibRefCitation>
, but later raised to the species level (
<bibRefCitation box="[348,537,474,499]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref19634" refString="Kuznetsov, V. I. (1958) Zwei arten der gattung Evergestis Hb. (Lepidoptera, Pyralididae) aus West-Kopet-Dagh (Turkmenia). Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 37, 929 - 932." type="book chapter">Kuznetsov 1958</bibRefCitation>
). In the only male deposited at the 
<collectionCode box="[927,1006,475,498]" country="Spain" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/gj99-xj2c" name="Jard� Bot�nic Marimurtra" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">HMIM</collectionCode>
some traces of cornuti were observed, while in the examined 
<typeStatus box="[406,505,511,535]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">paratype</typeStatus>
, cornuti were entirely visible, although being very small (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1279,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1948,1970]" captionTargetBox="[156,1387,509,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,445,1927]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia. A, D, G) Evergestis comealis stat. n. B, E, H) E. shirazalis, Paratype. C, F, I) E. infirmalis. A, B, C: main body and phallus. D, E, F: posterior end including uncus and gnathos in lateral (D, F) and ventral (E) views. G, H, I: distal end of phallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1247148/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 7B, H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
